<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="396" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1562,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1634,1660]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The larva of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[480,758,1634,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis box="[480,758,1634,1660]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Acanthagrion truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
fits better on the Group II, by presenting rounded cephalic lobes, 7-segmented antennae, acute apex of caudal lamellae, and 2 or 2+ 
<subScript attach="left" box="[967,975,1689,1703]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">1</subScript>
premental setae on each side of midline. It occurs in sympatry with other three Group II species in the collecting site (due to the presence of larvae and/or adults): 
<taxonomicName authority="Tennessen, 2004" authorityName="Tennessen" authorityYear="2004" box="[245,585,1742,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aepiolum">
<emphasis box="[245,383,1742,1769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. aepiolum</emphasis>
Tennessen, 2004
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rambur, 1842)" baseAuthorityName="Rambur" baseAuthorityYear="1842" box="[599,902,1742,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis box="[599,712,1742,1769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. gracile</emphasis>
(Rambur, 1842)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Selys, 1876" authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[963,1218,1742,1769]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lancea">
<emphasis box="[963,1071,1742,1769]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. lancea</emphasis>
Selys, 1876
</taxonomicName>
. According to data available on literature and examined material (we did not examined larvae material from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tennessen" authorityYear="2004" box="[1143,1278,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aepiolum">
<emphasis box="[1143,1278,1778,1805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. aepiolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[1331,1437,1778,1805]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lancea">
<emphasis box="[1331,1437,1778,1805]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. lancea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[256,403,1815,1841]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis box="[256,403,1815,1841]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae can be distinguished by lacking 3 premental setae in any of the midline sides, which occurs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[261,368,1850,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lancea">
<emphasis box="[261,368,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. lancea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Anjos-Santos et al. 2011)" baseAuthorityName="Anjos-Santos" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[424,842,1850,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gracile">
<emphasis box="[424,534,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. gracile</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Anjos-Santos, D. &amp; Carrico, C. &amp; Costa, J. M. &amp; Santos, T. C." box="[550,835,1850,1876]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" pagination="44 - 50" refId="ref2927" refString="Anjos-Santos, D., Carrico, C., Costa, J. M. &amp; Santos, T. C. (2011) Description of the final instar larvae of Acanthagrion gracile (Rambur) and Acanthagrion lancea Selys (Odonata: Coenagrionidae). Zootaxa, 2832 (1), 44 - 50. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2832.1.2" type="journal article" year="2011">
Anjos-Santos 
<emphasis box="[710,767,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">et al.</emphasis>
2011
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Larvae of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tennessen" authorityYear="2004" box="[970,1106,1850,1877]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aepiolum">
<emphasis box="[970,1106,1850,1877]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. aepiolum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also lacks 3 premental setae, however some specimens presented six antennomeres (
<bibRefCitation author="Lozano, F. &amp; Garre, A. &amp; Pessacq, P." box="[775,994,1886,1912]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref3158" refString="Lozano, F., Garre, A. &amp; Pessacq, P. (2007) Descripcion del ultimo estadio larval de Acanthagrion aepiolum (Odonata: Coenagrionidae). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 66 (1 - 2), 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="2007">
Lozano 
<emphasis box="[869,926,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), which we did not observed in the examined specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[396,543,1923,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="truncatum">
<emphasis box="[396,543,1923,1949]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">A. truncatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<tableCitation box="[603,686,1922,1948]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,239,1438,1462]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphological differences between some Group II (Sensu Novelo-Gutiérrez 2009) species occurring in sympatry with A. truncatum." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0B21C19D2C0148FF19A59EFE4E98F4" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" tableUuid="DF0B21C19D2C0148FF19A59EFE4E98F4">Table 1</tableCitation>
). Other traits such as mandibular formula, total body length shape of apical caudal lamellae, and number of palpal setae are very similar between these four species and also other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Selys" authorityYear="1876" box="[151,305,1994,2020]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Acanthagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,305,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">Acanthagrion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
larvae, thus not being reliable diagnostic characters (
<bibRefCitation author="Roman-Heracleo, J. &amp; Springer, M. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R." box="[901,1225,1994,2021]" pageId="3" pageNumber="396" pagination="219 - 229" refId="ref3301" refString="Roman-Heracleo, J., Springer, M. &amp; Novelo-Gutierrez, R. (2019) Descriptions of the larvae of Acanthagrion speculum and A. trilobatum from Costa Rica (Odonata: Coenagrionidae). Zootaxa, 4624 (2), 219 - 229. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4624.2.5" type="journal article" year="2019">
Román-Heracleo 
<emphasis box="[1101,1150,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="396">et al</emphasis>
. 2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
